d compare results.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI experiment revealed that pure threshold approaches fail due to the \"Constant Format Problem\" - tokens with CFI=1.00 and freq�160 are metaprogramming artifacts with zero information content. The proposed solution is a hybrid scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120). This needs to be tested against the previous results.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate and run the Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment (Strategy C) using the existing 200-pulse dataset, comparing hybrid scoring against the binary threshold approach to validate whether continuous scoring outperforms discrete filtering.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFIxFreq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Goal:** Test continuous scoring formula vs binary thresholds\r\n\r\n## Scoring Formula\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n- **Dataset:** 200 pulses from previous CFI experiment\r\n- **Split:** 160 train / 40 test (same as previous)\r\n- **Compare:**\r\n  - Strategy A: freq-only threshold (�60)\r\n  - Strategy B: CFI-only threshold (�0.7 AND freq<60)\r\n  - Strategy C: Hybrid score(T) � 0.3\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n```powershell\r\n# Calculate hybrid scores\r\n$hybridScore = $cfi * [Math]::Min(1, $freq / 120)\r\n\r\n# Find optimal threshold via grid search on training set\r\n$thresholds = @(0.1, 0.15, 0.2, 0.25, 0.3, 0.35, 0.4, 0.5)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Results (Pending)\r\n- [ ] Run experiment\r\n- [ ] Compare precision/recall against Strategies A and B\r\n- [ ] Determine if hybrid scoring outperforms binary filtering\r\n\r\n## Key Question\r\nDoes score(T) = CFI x min(1, freq/120) properly distinguish:\r\n- \"for next instantiation\" (freq=160, CFI=1.00)  score=1.0 (but should be LOW)\r\n- \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96)  score=0.96 (research trajectory)\r\n- \"research/CFI_COMPRESSION\" (freq=12, CFI=0.85)  score=0.085 (should be HIGH)\r\n\r\n## Risk\r\nThe hybrid formula still gives high scores to constant-format tokens.\r\nNeed to verify if the min(freq/120) penalty is sufficient.\r\n```\r\nfile: research/HYBRID_SCORING_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:50:36"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1239,"aggregated":"File: pulse_2026-03-24 125015.md\r\n---\r\n# Pulse: 2026-03-24 125015\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: the (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me review where we are in the research:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE - Architecture cross-analysis and integration spec done\r\n2. Gap-Decay Synthesis done - session gaps are compression\r\n3. CFI Compression Experiment done - key finding that CFI�0.7 AND freq<60 is too aggressive\r\n4. NEW INSIGHT - Constant Format Problem identified: tokens like freq=160, CFI=1.00 are metaprogramming artifacts\r\n\r\nThe next step from the notes is:\r\n- \"Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\"\r\n- The scoring formula proposed is: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nI need to run a hybrid scoring experiment. Let me check what data we have available. The previous experiment results are in `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`.\r\n\r\nLooking at the notes:\r\n- CFI gives +32.9% precision but loses 92.9% recall\r\n- Three-dimensional filter: CFI � 0.5 AND freq � 3 AND freq < 120\r\n- Hybrid scoring: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nI should run this experiment now. The most concrete action would be to:\r\n1. Implement the hybrid scoring experiment\r\n2. Compare it against the previous binary threshold approach\r\n\r\nLet me check if there's pulse data available. Looking at the recent pulse file: `pulse_2026-03-24 124915.md`. There should be 200 pulses worth of data from the CFI experiment.\r\n\r\nThe action I should take: Run the hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment (Strategy C) as noted in the pending items.\r\n\r\nI need to create a PowerShell script to analyze the existing pulse data using the hybrid scoring formula and compare results.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI experiment revealed that pure threshold approaches fail due to the \"Constant Format Problem\" - tokens with CFI=1.00 and freq�160 are metaprogramming artifacts with zero information content. The proposed solution is a hybrid scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120). This needs to be tested against the previous results.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate and run the Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment (Strategy C) using the existing 200-pulse dataset, comparing hybrid scoring against the binary threshold approach to validate whether continuous scoring outperforms discrete filtering.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFIxFreq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Goal:** Test continuous scoring formula vs binary thresholds\r\n\r\n## Scoring Formula\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n- **Dataset:** 200 pulses from previous CFI experiment\r\n- **Split:** 160 train / 40 test (same as previous)\r\n- **Compare:**\r\n  - Strategy A: freq-only threshold (�60)\r\n  - Strategy B: CFI-only threshold (�0.7 AND freq<60)\r\n  - Strategy C: Hybrid score(T) � 0.3\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n```powershell\r\n# Calculate hybrid scores\r\n$hybridScore = $cfi * [Math]::Min(1, $freq / 120)\r\n\r\n# Find optimal threshold via grid search on training set\r\n$thresholds = @(0.1, 0.15, 0.2, 0.25, 0.3, 0.35, 0.4, 0.5)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Results (Pending)\r\n- [ ] Run experiment\r\n- [ ] Compare precision/recall against Strategies A and B\r\n- [ ] Determine if hybrid scoring outperforms binary filtering\r\n\r\n## Key Question\r\nDoes score(T) = CFI x min(1, freq/120) properly distinguish:\r\n- \"for next instantiation\" (freq=160, CFI=1.00)  score=1.0 (but should be LOW)\r\n- \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96)  score=0.96 (research trajectory)\r\n- \"research/CFI_COMPRESSION\" (freq=12, CFI=0.85)  score=0.085 (should be HIGH)\r\n\r\n## Risk\r\nThe hybrid formula still gives high scores to constant-format tokens.\r\nNeed to verify if the min(freq/120) penalty is sufficient.\r\n```\r\nfile: research/HYBRID_SCORING_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:50:36","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774371098432}}
