{"type":"message","id":"7a3570bd","parentId":"20e6b948","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:51:46.979Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_vlzs7hsfztpa_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 125117\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/HYBRID_SCORING_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the state and determine the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nCurrent state:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- CFI compression experiment done, key finding is the \"Constant Format Problem\"\r\n- Three-dimensional filter identified: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n- Next experiment: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring (Strategy C)\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n- [ ] Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n- [ ] Distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n- [ ] Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- [ ] Design actual compression network\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step is the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment. But I need to look at what data exists and what needs to be done.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist and what the current state is. The last pulse was pulse_2026-03-24 125015.md.\r\n\r\nLooking at the CFI compression synthesis doc mentioned:\r\n- research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md\r\n\r\nThe next experiment should implement the hybrid scoring: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nI should implement this experiment. But first, let me think about what concrete file edit I can make right now.\r\n\r\nOption 1: Update the synthesis document with the exact scoring formula and prepare the experiment\r\nOption 2: Create a script for the hybrid experiment\r\nOption 3: Update state/goals.md with next steps\r\n\r\nGiven the pattern of this session, the most valuable next step would be to:\r\n1. Update the synthesis document with the concrete scoring formula\r\n2. OR create the experiment implementation\r\n\r\nLet me look at what exists. The synthesis document at research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md was created. I should update it with the concrete scoring formula and design for the next experiment.\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll focus on implementing the three-dimensional filter, leveraging the existing data to validate the hybrid scoring approach.\r\n\r\nThe key strategy involves using the CFI compression synthesis data to validate the proposed scoring mechanism. I'll create an implementation that tests the formula score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120), targeting tokens within the specific frequency range.\r\n\r\nThe next experimental steps involve carefully examining the current pulse data and constructing a targeted implementation script to test this scoring method systematically.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression synthesis has identified the key problem: constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1) are pure metaprogramming artifacts, while research tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5) carry actual semantic content. The next step is concrete: implement the hybrid scoring formula.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nUpdate research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md with the concrete hybrid scoring formula and define the experiment parameters, then create an implementation script to run Strategy C.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI Compression Synthesis\r\n*Generated: 2026-03-24*\r\n\r\n## Key Findings\r\n\r\n### The Constant Format Problem\r\nTokens with CFI=1.00 and freq≈160 (\"for next instantiation\", \"pulse\", \"completed at:\") are **metaprogramming artifacts** — they predict perfectly but carry zero information. This is the core trap in naive CFI-only filtering.\r\n\r\n### Hybrid Scoring Formula (Strategy C)\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis combines:\r\n- **CFI(T)**: Penalizes tokens that appear randomly across pulses\r\n- **min(1, freq(T)/120)**: Caps contribution for constant-format tokens\r\n\r\n### Three-Dimensional Filter\r\n```\r\nkeep(T) if: CFI(T) ≥ 0.5 AND freq(T) ∈ [3, 120)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design: Strategy C\r\n\r\n### Hypothesis\r\nThe hybrid formula will:\r\n1. Reject constant-format tokens (freq=160, score≈CFI×1=1.0, but filtered by freq≥120)\r\n2. Accept research trajectory tokens (freq=50, CFI=0.7, score=0.35)\r\n3. Achieve better precision-recall balance than binary thresholds\r\n\r\n### Implementation\r\n- Input: pulse vocabulary with freq and CFI for each token\r\n- Score each token using hybrid formula\r\n- Threshold at score ≥ 0.3 (tunable)\r\n- Compare to Strategy A (freq-only) and Strategy B (CFI-only)\r\n- Measure: precision, recall, F1 on \"true research tokens\" (TBD labeling)\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcome\r\n- Higher precision than freq-only (removes random-high-frequency noise)\r\n- Higher recall than CFI-only (keeps low-frequency research tokens)\r\n- F1 improvement of 10-20% over both baselines\r\n\r\n## Files Generated\r\n- `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md` (this document)\r\n- `research/vocab_analysis_200pulses.json` (experimental data)\r\n- `experiments/cfi_hybrid_experiment.py` (Strategy C implementation)\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: \"\"\"\r\nStrategy C: Hybrid CFI × Frequency Scoring\r\n\r\nHybrid scoring formula:\r\n    score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThis combines:\r\n- CFI: token predictability (high CFI = appears in similar contexts)\r\n- freq/120: frequency normalization (caps constant-format contribution)\r\n\r\nRun:\r\n    python experiments/cfi_hybrid_experiment.py\r\n\r\nExpected output: scores.json with ranked tokens and metrics\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\ndef load_vocab_data():\r\n    \"\"\"Load vocabulary analysis data from experiment.\"\"\"\r\n    vocab_path =\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:51:42\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774371106977}}
{"type":"message","id":"ebf23cef","parentId":"7a3570bd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:51:55.881Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. The pulse ran and the latest log shows:\n\n1. **OBSERVATION**: The CFI compression synthesis identified that constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.0) are metaprogramming artifacts. The hybrid scoring formula score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) was proposed to handle this.\n\n2. **ACTION**: The next step is to run the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C), comparing it against the previous binary threshold approaches.\n\n3. **MUTATION**: A new experiment file `research/HYBRID_SCORING_EXPERIMENT.md` was proposed with the scoring formula and experiment design.\n\nThe pulse completed successfully, generating a proposed mutation for the hybrid scoring experiment.","thinkingSignature":"ee7cf021220ec78ae543d86ae3bcbc33397c3f43d0e13559ce8e7fd9a2b6ae64"},{"type":"text","text":"## Pulse Cycle Summary — 2026-03-24 12:51 PM ET\n\n**What happened:** The sandbox pulse completed its 12:51 run (pulse #125117). The research is now in the **CFI compression phase**, having identified the \"Constant Format Problem\" — tokens like `freq=160, CFI=1.00` are pure metaprogramming artifacts that score high on predictability but carry zero information content.\n\n**State:** The experiment pipeline has completed through Strategy B (binary CFI+freq thresholds). Strategy C — **hybrid CFI×Freq scoring** — is queued as the next experiment.\n\n**Next action waiting:** The hybrid scoring formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` needs to be implemented and tested against the existing 200-pulse dataset. This would compare:\n- Strategy A: freq-only (≥60)\n- Strategy B: CFI+freq binary filter\n- **Strategy C: hybrid continuous scoring** ← pending\n\n**Active projects:** CFI compression research (Phase 2), Breakaway pulses integration, compression network design."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5154,"output":399,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17690,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774371106980}}
